<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14178">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Truck%20Transportation.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3352">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      List the major truck lines serving your town. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://www.quicktransportsolutions.com/quickfreight/loadboard/carrier-searchby-citystate.php"
        target="_blank"
        >Search Trucking Companies - Find Carriers By City And State
        (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3353">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3353 mb-requirement-id-3354">
        (a) Describe the role of truck transportation within commerce (the
        movement of goods, funds, and information). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/j4EfFO-MAoY" target="_blank"
          >10 Advantages of Road Transport (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3353 mb-requirement-id-3355">
        (b) Describe how trucks fit into a company's supply chain. This could be
        a manufacturer, importer, wholesaler, or retailer. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kMm-13EdnqA" target="_blank"
          >Transportation &amp; Logistics Industry Overview - Introduction
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6ScpuV1aStM" target="_blank"
          >How Does Trucking Fit Into the Supply Chain? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://considerblog.com/transportation/the-vital-role-of-trucks-in-transporting-goods-a-comprehensive-overview.html"
          target="_blank"
          >The Vital Role of Trucks in Transporting Goods: A Comprehensive
          Overview (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3353 mb-requirement-id-3356">
        (c) On paper, map out how goods that are manufactured overseas are
        transported to a retailer in this country. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fdg9nhmZuJw" target="_blank"
          >Global Supply Chain Management Explained: Key Players, Risks &amp;
          Incoterms (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3357">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Describe the difference between the gasoline engine and the diesel engine
      that power trucks. List the advantages of each. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/3G9x6U3VkwQ" target="_blank"
        >Diesel vs. Gasoline Engines: Key Differences Explained (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3358">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Visit a truck terminal and complete items 4(a) through 4(e). After your
      visit, share what you have learned with your counselor.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3358 mb-requirement-id-3359">
        (a) Find out what kind of maintenance program the company follows to
        help keep its fleet, drivers, and the roadway safe. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bQcm9irqKIk" target="_blank"
          >How To Properly Maintain Fleets? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7dXo-RlPc8A" target="_blank"
          >How Trucking Companies Manage Fleet Maintenance Effectively | Part 1
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tGrxcFCukJs" target="_blank"
          >How Trucking Companies Manage Fleet Maintenance Effectively | Part 2
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3358 mb-requirement-id-3360">
        (b) Find out how dispatchers maintain communication with drivers on the
        road. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Pv9-ZKoWNww" target="_blank"
          >Communication with Dispatch (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3358 mb-requirement-id-3361">
        (c) Talk with a professional truck driver about safety. Learn about the
        truck driver's rules of the road for safe driving. List five
        safe-driving rules every professional truck driver must follow. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/poVtx0v1TG4" target="_blank"
          >Top 6 Safety Tips for Truck Drivers (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aQi1QlMQv4Q" target="_blank"
          >Essential Safety Tips, Every Female Trucker Needs to Stay Safe
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3358 mb-requirement-id-3362">
        (d) Review the driver's log and find out what kind of information the
        log contains. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.safetyvideos.com/how-to-fill-out-a-logbook-for-cdl-drivers"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Fill Out a Logbook for CDL Drivers (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3358 mb-requirement-id-3363">
        (e) Learn about important federal regulations that help ensure public
        safety. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/regulations" target="_blank"
          >Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA) - Regulations
          Overview (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/aHI1-vEt2qE" target="_blank"
          >Federal Safety Regulations Limit a Long-Haul Truck Driver's Time on
          the Road (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/SpmOiaa64LQ" target="_blank"
          >Federal Regulations Every Truck Driver Should Know! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3364">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3364 mb-requirement-id-3365">
        (a) Outline the general organization of a trucking company. Describe
        what each department does.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3364 mb-requirement-id-3366">
        (b) List five positions with trucking companies and describe each one.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.bestyetexpresstrucking.com/jobs-in-the-trucking-industry/?utm_source=chatgpt.com"
          target="_blank"
          >14 Jobs in the Trucking Industry Other Than Driving (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3367">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Name five government agencies that work closely with the trucking
      industry. Describe their role. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://www.osha.gov/trucking-industry/other-federal-agencies"
        target="_blank"
        >Trucking Industry (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3368">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      List five different kinds of trucks. Tell the service each provides.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/wMil4tzaOcU" target="_blank"
        >Different Types of Trucks and Their Uses (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3369">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Assume that you are going to ship by truck 500 pounds of goods (freight
      class 65) from your town to another town 500 miles away. Your shipment
      must arrive within three days. Explain in writing:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3369 mb-requirement-id-3370">
        (a) How to prepare the shipment <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/xZqB2-jTows?si=AtPDbOqNDr8aWCLi"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Prepare Freight for Shipping to Avoid Damages (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UEaNCBHQVZc?si=UrYkr7yNQgw-6Te3"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Ship A Pallet: Preparing A Palletized LTL Freight Shipment
          Warehousing Tutorial (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/478XjiLWg80?si=nplGRI0kARBcrtE9"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Package Freight for Shipping (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3369 mb-requirement-id-3371">
        (b) How to compare at least three carriers for time in transit and rates
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CGhqH0849cs" target="_blank"
          >Mastering Load Board Bookings: A Step-by-Step Guide to Efficient Load
          Booking (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-yppE9CJ2Yk" target="_blank"
          >Truck Dispatcher and Broker Call Simulation - Negotiation Scenario #1
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3369 mb-requirement-id-3372">
        (c) How to choose which carrier to use
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3369 mb-requirement-id-3373">
        (d) How to insure the shipment for damages <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.flockfreight.com/blog/understanding-freight-shipping-insurance-a-comprehensive-guide?utm_source=chatgpt.com"
          target="_blank"
          >Understanding Freight Shipping Insurance: A Comprehensive Guide
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3374">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Explain the following terms: bill of lading, ETA, logbook, intermodal,
      containers, tariff, shippers, carrier, consignee, drayage, and cartage.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/0H0Q0VNLMu4?si=91WiYyuzDzCTWV2r" target="_blank"
        >Decoding Freight Abbreviations, Acronyms and Initialisms (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/cSp3ryfdyFM?si=rPSekMOLuDdcueKb" target="_blank"
        >What's That? Bill of Lading (BOL) (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/GSWxDr6mt8c?si=b1VrZKtrLyYmUMLm" target="_blank"
        >What's That? Intermodal &amp; Multimodal (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/UlstPHRwhA8?si=DJa8Oa9evpW0wc7B" target="_blank"
        >What's That? Container vs. Trailer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3375">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Explore careers related to this merit badge. Research one career to learn
      about the training and education needed, costs, job prospects, salary, job
      duties, and career advancement. Your research methods may include—with
      your parent or guardian's permission—an internet or library search, an
      interview with a professional in the field, or a visit to a location where
      people in this career work. Discuss with your counselor both your findings
      and what about this profession might make it an interesting career.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TJGXJwNyw8U?si=y5Qr4fDUORdf3lZY" target="_blank"
        >What Career Opportunities are in Trucking? A LOT! (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/CiAbSIXwMSs?si=YT7HzX_P99DskdIn" target="_blank"
        >What Life Is Like for a Trucker on the Road | NewsNation (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/hbJqSgcQWj8?si=pwS-oHaKebXXdijD" target="_blank"
        >How to Become a Truck Dispatcher in 5 Steps? - Beginner Training
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/MbmX3ZAjHbw?si=ddep_jZOj9FLgQEC" target="_blank"
        >Logistics Coordinator Job Description (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/zVZ3RASiXoA?si=FhUizvScSxHerKZy" target="_blank"
        >5 Must Have Skills to earn $10,000 a month as a Truck Dispatcher
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
